<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15509">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Reading.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15510">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15510 mb-requirement-id-15511">
        (a) Take a tour of a library. Discuss with your counselor how the
        library is organized and what resources and/or services are offered in
        the library. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wm3OYbqWGt4" target="_blank"
          >How Is a Library Organized (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Vq_nXCKqvvI?si=GIOeyfCbat453Qtp"
          target="_blank"
          >Library of Congress Classification (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15510 mb-requirement-id-15512">
        (b) Learn how to search for material using a library's card catalog or
        computerized catalog by author, title, and subject.<br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/bBoBFioGVJc?si=W5X75XCeu-dxS8if"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use a Card Catalog (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15510 mb-requirement-id-15513">
        (c) In a library, search the card catalog or computerized catalog for
        six books of four different types, such as poetry, fiction, nonfiction,
        and biographies. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yqg41rMDlKA" target="_blank"
          >Locating a Book in a Library (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15510 mb-requirement-id-15514">
        (d) With the assistance of your counselor or the librarian, see if you
        can locate on the shelves the six books you selected.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15510 mb-requirement-id-15515">
        (e) Explain what a library card is, why it is needed, and how to get
        one. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/LOhNkY0yb4s?si=fCdFQINKX1P4wNYJ"
          target="_blank"
          >How Do I...Get a Library Card (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15516">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15516 mb-requirement-id-15517">
        (a) Identify a book you have enjoyed. Find out what other books the
        author has written.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15516 mb-requirement-id-15518">
        (b) Look at one or more "best books" lists. These can be based on year,
        subject, or even all time. Identify at least one book you would like to
        read. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wPDAjvQCgIg" target="_blank"
          >Best Selling Books Ever (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/_FWW0V4rwj4" target="_blank"
          >10 Most Read Books of All Time (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15519">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Read four different types of books, such as poetry, fiction, nonfiction,
      or biographies. Do one of the following for each book you have read:
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/aPVgS3CI5SU?si=OkVFctCrfbNYCegr" target="_blank"
        >Every Book Genre Explained (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/mQINQAxu-5k?si=dNoZJStT4sCeK5NA" target="_blank"
        >Literary Genres: Nonfiction (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/G5GUUgHVruQ?si=Vb-wmUTGtTSsRvDN" target="_blank"
        >How to Get Into Poetry as a Beginner (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15519 mb-requirement-id-15520">
        (a) Write a review of the book. Include what you liked and/or didn't
        like about the book. Include whether you would recommend this book, and
        if so, who might enjoy reading it. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/IhYF3v3zTeo" target="_blank"
          >How to Write a Book Review (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/BJfKSm0VpuU?si=IsukhqXWGXupIMa1"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Write a Book Review (12 Steps) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15519 mb-requirement-id-15521">
        (b) Watch a movie based on the book. What was the same between the book
        and movie? What was different? Which did you enjoy more? Discuss this
        with your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ho70o1kiwf4" target="_blank"
          >7 Big Differences (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15519 mb-requirement-id-15522">
        (c) Give a book talk to your class, troop, or patrol. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/XoHzONEs5Uw" target="_blank"
          >How to Do a Book Talk (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15529">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Read a nonfiction book or magazine that teaches you how to do something
      like cooking, wood-building projects, video game design, science
      experiments, knot-tying, etc. With your counselor's and parent or
      guardian's permission, complete a project from the book. Share your
      experience with your counselor. Reading a merit badge pamphlet will not
      count toward completing this requirement. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/3nLX0CjMO-Q?si=4SNTBq8jqKAhZioe" target="_blank"
        >How to Improve Reading Comprehension (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15530">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Read about the world around you from any two sources: books, magazines,
      newspapers, the internet (with your parent or guardian's permission),
      field manuals, etc. Topics may include Scouting, sports, environmental
      problems, politics, social issues, current events, nature, religion, etc.
      Discuss what you have learned with your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/LbO3lRXT0ww?si=GDgqXvC8Jw_0S09p" target="_blank"
        >Summarizing Main Ideas (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15523">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      With your counselor's and parent or guardian's permission, choose ONE of
      the following activities and devote at least four hours of service to that
      activity. Discuss your participation with your counselor.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15523 mb-requirement-id-15524">
        (a) Read to a sick, blind, or homebound person in a hospital or in an
        extended-care facility. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sxdINJaZ9q4" target="_blank"
          >Tips on Reading Out Loud (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15523 mb-requirement-id-15525">
        (b) Perform volunteer work at your school library or a public library.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/XhAR6VUfzBU?si=TCckKMIiB1Xllwgq"
          target="_blank"
          >Teen Volunteer Opportunities (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15523 mb-requirement-id-15526">
        (c) Read stories to younger children, in a group or individually.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/iRPNPCAf84E" target="_blank"
          >Top Tips for Reading to Children (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15523 mb-requirement-id-15527">
        (d) Organize a book swap in your troop, school, or place of worship.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/jRX9vZqx4AI?si=IViwsmilodCCMP7L"
          target="_blank"
          >Host a Book Swap Party (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15523 mb-requirement-id-15528">
        (e) Organize a book drive to collect books. Donate them to an
        organization in need. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/W9G0X6gAhwY" target="_blank"
          >Brag Book (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15531">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Identify three career opportunities that would use skills and knowledge in
      reading. Pick one and research the training, education, certification
      requirements, experience, and expenses associated with entering the field.
      Research the prospects for employment, starting salary, advancement
      opportunities and career goals associated with this career. Discuss what
      you learned with your counselor and whether you might be interested in
      this career.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
